<subSubSection id="5CBC65591871FFE7FF35F89F4D54F8BE" pageId="6" pageNumber="492" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="141936D21871FFE7FF35F89F4D54F8BE" blockId="6.[151,1437,1116,1897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="492">
<emphasis id="26D2EAC01871FFE7FF35F89F490FF8F7" bold="true" box="[199,308,1800,1825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="492">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="D3A64D511871FFE7FEB0F89F49DCF8F6" box="[322,487,1800,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mishmiensis">
<emphasis id="26D2EAC01871FFE7FEB0F89F49DCF8F6" box="[322,487,1800,1824]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="492">S. mishmiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="D3A64D511871FFE7FD8BF89F4AC8F8F7" authority="Li" authorityName="Li" box="[633,755,1800,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi">
<emphasis id="26D2EAC01871FFE7FD8BF89F4AE8F8F6" box="[633,723,1800,1824]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="492">S. yangi</emphasis>
Li
</taxonomicName>
in having brushlike setae on the dorsal margin of the ventral process of the aedeagus but differs in having a much longer pygofer process and more elongate head which is depressed and without an anterior marginal keel. It is uniformly creamy white compared to greenish 
<emphasis id="26D2EAC01871FFE7FB0CF8C74D54F8BE" box="[1278,1391,1872,1896]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="492">
<taxonomicName id="D3A64D511871FFE7FB0CF8C74D50F8BE" box="[1278,1387,1872,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lunglei">S. lunglei</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
